5.3.7 Tickler [I]
-----------------

*What it is*: Items with a specific review date - things you want to be
reminded about at a future time.

   *When to use it*: For ideas, projects, or actions you're not ready
for NOW but want to reconsider on a specific date.

   *Examples*:
   • Project paused until Q2 starts (review on April 1st)
   • Check if new API is released (review monthly)
   • Consider kitchen remodel when bonus arrives (review in June)
   • Revisit proposal after team meeting (review next week)

   *What org-gtd does*:
   • Prompts for review date
   • Sets ‘ORG_GTD_TIMESTAMP’ property with the date
   • Refiles to tickler file
   • Will remind you in agenda on that date to reconsider

   *Use case - Paused projects*: You can tickler entire projects to
temporarily hide them from your active views while preserving all
structure and dependencies.  See *note Tickler Projects: Tickler
Projects Pausing Work You're Not Ready For. for details.

   *State Preservation*: Like someday items, tickler saves your item's
current state (‘ORG_GTD’, TODO keyword, and type-specific properties
like ‘DELEGATED_TO’).  When the review date arrives and you run ‘M-x
org-gtd-reactivate’, you'll be prompted to confirm or update each
property.

   *GTD principle*: The tickler file is a time-based reminder system.
Items appear when the date arrives, prompting you to decide if you're
ready to act.


