5.3.10 Knowledge [K]
--------------------

*What it is*: Reference information to store for later.

   *When to use it*: When the item is information to keep, not an action
to take.

   *Examples*:
   • Recipe you want to remember
   • Quote from article
   • Meeting notes for reference
   • Product specifications

   *Important*: Choose this AFTER you've properly stored the information
somewhere (your notes system, wiki, etc.).  This just marks the inbox
item as "filed" and archives it.

   *GTD principle*: Separate "stuff to do" from "stuff to know."
Knowledge goes in your reference system, not your action lists.


