5.4.6 Tutorial: Complex Dependencies with Graph View
----------------------------------------------------

   • The Scenario

     "Release Next Version of Software":

       1. List features (starting task)
       2. Implement features (depends on list)
       3. Write documentation (can start after list, parallel with
          implement)
       4. Get beta tester feedback (depends on both implement AND
          documentation)
       5. Update code based on feedback (depends on beta feedback)
       6. Update documentation based on feedback (depends on beta
          feedback, parallel with code updates)
       7. Release (depends on both updates completing)

   • The Dependency Graph

          List Features
              ├──→ Implement Features ───┐
              └──→ Write Documentation ───┼──→ Get Beta Feedback
                                          │         ├──→ Update Code ─────┐
                                          │         └──→ Update Docs ──────┼──→ Release
                                          └───────────────────────────────┘

   • Building with Graph View

     Starting from the project heading, open the command menu with ‘?’:

       1. ‘a r’ → "List features" (root task)
       2. Select "List features"
       3. ‘a s’ → "Implement features" → check "List features" → RET
       4. Go back to "List features"
       5. ‘a s’ → "Write documentation" → check "List features" → RET

     Now you have two parallel branches from "List features".

   • Creating the Convergence Point

     For "Get Beta Feedback" that depends on BOTH implement AND
     documentation:

       1. Select "Implement features"
       2. ‘a s’ → "Get Beta Feedback"
       3. In the checkbox menu, check BOTH "Implement features" AND
          "Write documentation"
       4. Press ‘RET’

     Now "Get Beta Feedback" has two blockers - it won't become NEXT
     until both are complete.

   • Building the Rest

     Continue building the parallel update paths:

       1. Select "Get Beta Feedback"
       2. ‘a s’ → "Update code" → check "Get Beta Feedback" → RET
       3. Select "Get Beta Feedback" again
       4. ‘a s’ → "Update docs" → check "Get Beta Feedback" → RET

     For the final convergence at "Release":

       1. Select "Update code"
       2. ‘a s’ → "Release"
       3. Check BOTH "Update code" AND "Update docs"
       4. Press ‘RET’

   • The Complete Graph

                     [List Features - NEXT]
                        /              \
                       ↓                ↓
          [Implement - TODO]    [Write Docs - TODO]
                       \                /
                        ↓              ↓
                   [Get Beta Feedback - TODO]
                        /              \
                       ↓                ↓
             [Update Code - TODO]  [Update Docs - TODO]
                        \              /
                         ↓            ↓
                      [Release - TODO]

   • Key Patterns This Example Shows

       1. *Parallel branches* from List Features (using ‘a s’ twice from
          same parent)
       2. *Converging paths* at Get Beta Feedback (using multi-select
          checkbox)
       3. *Parallel updates* after feedback (using ‘a s’ twice)
       4. *Final convergence* at Release (using multi-select checkbox)

     All four patterns are fully supported.


