5.4.23 Defining your own agenda views
-------------------------------------

You can define your own agenda views by defining functions with custom
agenda commands.  As long as you have ‘org-gtd-directory’ in your
‘org-agenda-files’ (required for org-gtd to work), your views will
include GTD items automatically.

     (defun my-agenda ()
       (let ((org-agenda-custom-commands '(your-definition-here)))
         (org-agenda nil "x")))

   Where ‘x’ is whatever your defined key is.

   *See also*: For a much easier way to create custom views, see *note
View DSL Filter Reference::, which provides a declarative language for
defining views without writing skip functions.


