6.5.4 Filter Reference
----------------------

The following sections document all available filters.  Use them to
build the exact view you need.

   • View Structure

     A GTD view is defined as an alist with filters at the top level:

          ;; Simple view with filters at top level
          '((name . "View Name")
            (type . delegated)
            (when . past))

     Multiple filters create AND logic (all must match).

        • Multi-Block Views

          For complex views with multiple sections (like the engage
          view), use ‘blocks’:

               '((name . "My Custom Dashboard")
                 (blocks . (((name . "Today's Calendar")
                             (block-type . calendar-day))
                            ((name . "Items Due Today")
                             (type . delegated)
                             (when . today))
                            ((name . "All NEXT Actions")
                             (type . next-action)))))

          Each block is its own view spec.  Blocks are displayed in
          order as separate agenda sections.

        • Block Types

          Special ‘block-type’ values control how blocks are rendered:

          ‘calendar-day’
               Native org-agenda day view filtered to Calendar and Habit
               items only
          ‘todo’
               Native org-agenda todo block (requires ‘todo-keyword’)
          _default_
               org-ql query block (when no block-type specified)


