6.5.6 Time-based Filters
------------------------

Filter by timestamps, deadlines, and scheduled dates.

   • Semantic Time: ‘(when . VALUE)’

     The ‘when’ filter provides semantic time filtering that
     automatically uses the correct timestamp property for each GTD item
     type:

        • For ‘delegated’ and ‘calendar’ types: checks
          ‘ORG_GTD_TIMESTAMP’
        • For ‘tickler’ type: checks the tickler review date

     Values: ‘today’, ‘past’, ‘future’

     *Example*: Delegated items due today:
          '((name . "Delegated Check-ins Today")
            (type . delegated)
            (when . today))

     *Example*: Missed calendar appointments:
          '((name . "Missed Appointments")
            (type . calendar)
            (when . past))

     *Example*: Upcoming delegated check-ins:
          '((name . "Upcoming Delegated")
            (type . delegated)
            (when . future))

   • Deadline: ‘(deadline . VALUE)’

     Filter by org-mode DEADLINE.

     Values: ‘past’, ‘future’, ‘today’

     *Example*:
          '((name . "Overdue Items")
            (deadline . past))

   • Scheduled: ‘(scheduled . VALUE)’

     Filter by org-mode SCHEDULED.

     Values: ‘past’, ‘future’, ‘today’

     *Example*:
          '((name . "Today's Scheduled Items")
            (scheduled . today))


