6.5.7 *TODO* Keyword Filters
----------------------------

Filter by TODO state.

   *Note*: The ‘type’ filter automatically includes the correct TODO
keyword for each type (e.g., ‘next-action’ includes ‘NEXT’, ‘delegated’
includes ‘WAIT’).  Use these filters only when you need explicit
control.

   • ‘(todo . ("KEYWORD1" "KEYWORD2"))’

     *Matches*: Items with any of the specified TODO keywords

     *Use case*: Show specific states

     *Example*: Show only NEXT actions:
          '((name . "NEXT Actions Only")
            (todo . ("NEXT")))

     *Example*: Show NEXT and WAIT:
          '((name . "Active and Waiting")
            (todo . ("NEXT" "WAIT")))

   • ‘(done . VALUE)’

     *Matches*: Items with done TODO states (right side of ‘|’ in
     keyword sequence)

     *Values*:
     ‘t’
          Any done item, regardless of when closed
     ‘today’
          Done today
     ‘recent’
          Done in last 7 days
     ‘past-day’
          Done in last day
     ‘past-week’
          Done in last week
     ‘past-month’
          Done in last month
     ‘past-year’
          Done in last year

     *Use case*: Show completed items, optionally filtered by when they
     were completed

     *Example*: All completed items:
          '((name . "Completed Items")
            (done . t))

     *Example*: Items completed this week:
          '((name . "Completed This Week")
            (done . past-week))

     *Example*: Items completed today:
          '((name . "Completed Today")
            (done . today))


