6.6.6 Example Custom Hooks
--------------------------

   • Selective Tagging with Unless

     The most common pattern is "run this hook for everything EXCEPT
     certain types".  This example prompts for tags on all items except
     trash and knowledge (reference):

          (defun my-tag-tasks ()
            "Prompt for tags on all items except trash and knowledge."
            (unless (org-gtd-organize-type-member-p '(trash knowledge))
              (org-set-tags-command)))

          (setq org-gtd-organize-hooks '(my-tag-tasks))

     This replaces the default ‘org-set-tags-command’ with selective
     tagging.  The ‘unless’ pattern is cleaner than listing all the
     types you DO want: it says "skip these few, run for everything
     else."

   • Add Effort Estimation

          (defun my-add-effort ()
            "Prompt for effort estimation when organizing actions and projects."
            (when (org-gtd-organize-type-member-p '(action project))
              (call-interactively #'org-set-effort)))

          (add-to-list 'org-gtd-organize-hooks 'my-add-effort)

